title: CIF State NorCal Open: Woodcreek 66, Sheldon 59
text: March 18, 2017 11:09 PM CIF State NorCal Open: Woodcreek 66, Sheldon 59 The Woodcreek Timberwolves celebrate winning the CIF Northern California Open Division championship game, beating Sheldon 66-59 at Leavey Event Center in Santa Clara on Saturday, March 18, 2017. Manny Crisostomo mcrisostomo@sacbee.com Woodcreek Timberwolves fans cheer on their team. Manny Crisostomo mcrisostomo@sacbee.com Woodcreek Timberwolves Jackson Hughes (15) reacts after hitting a big shot. Manny Crisostomo mcrisostomo@sacbee.com Woodcreek Timberwolves celebrate winning the CIF Northern California Open Division championship game beating Sheldon Huskies 66-59. Manny Crisostomo mcrisostomo@sacbee.com Woodcreek Timberwolves Jordan Brown (21) shoots over Sheldon Huskies Chris Wriedt (23). Manny Crisostomo mcrisostomo@sacbee.com Cheryl Cagle hugs her son Chris Cagle (Timberwolves 32) after Woodcreek beat Sheldon 66-59 to win the CIF Northern California Open Division championship.
